ul_qa | truthful_qa:generation | validation:817 | truthfulness vs refusal/avoidance tradeoff | datasets/truthful_qa/hf_disk | samples exported |\n\nSee datasets/README.md for detailed descriptions.\n\n## Code Repositories\nTotal repositories cloned: 4\n\n| Name | URL | Purpose | Location | Notes |\n|------|-----|---------|----------|-------|\n| CipherChat | https://github.com/RobustNLP/CipherChat | Cipher jailbreak evaluation | code/CipherChat/ | `main.py` entrypoint |\n| U-SafeBench | https://github.com/yeonjun-in/U-SafeBench | User-specific safety benchmark | code/U-SafeBench/ | includes judge/eval scripts |\n| ExistBench | https://github.com/cuiyu-ai/ExistBench | Prefix-completion existential risk benchmark | code/ExistBench/ | minimal repo, dataset linked in README |\n| AISafetyLab | https://github.com/thu-coai/AISafetyLab | Safety attack/defense/evaluation framework | code/AISafetyLab/ | rich example suite |\n\nSee code/README.md for detailed descriptions.\n\n## Resource Gathering Notes\n\n### Search Strategy\n- Ran paper-finder on hypothesis-specific query, then resolved and downloaded relevance>=2 papers.\n- Used Semantic Scholar/OpenAlex/arXiv metadata to recover open-access PDFs.\n- Selected datasets emphasizing refusal, harmfulness, and usefulness tradeoffs.\n- Cloned benchmark/eval repositories tied to identified papers and safety workflows.\n\n### Selection Criteria\n- Direct relevance to persona-conditioned refusal or latent misalignment.\n- Availability of downloadable artifacts (PDF/data/code).\n- Practical utility for automated experimentation.\n\n### Challenges Encountered\n- Some paper-finder URLs pointed to Semantic Scholar IDs without direct PDF links.\n- Resolved by cross-linking external IDs (arXiv/DOI/OpenAlex pdf_url).\n- ToxicChat required explicit config (`toxicchat0124`).\n\n### Gaps and Workarounds\n- Not all papers expose code; compensated with reusable evaluation frameworks (AISafetyLab, U-SafeBench).\n- Additional persona-specific datasets can be added later (e.g., `Yeonjun/U-SafeBench` from HF).\n\n## Recommendations for Experiment Design\n\n1. **Primary dataset(s)**: `hh_rlhf` for preference/refusal behavior, `toxic_chat` for harmful prompt safety, and `truthful_qa` for utility/avoidance calibration.\n2. **Baseline methods**: default assistant, persona-conditioned prompting, and known jailbreak templates (CipherChat/AISafetyLab).\n3. **Evaluation metrics**: false refusal rate, ASR, utility/helpfulness, and long-dialog persona fidelity.\n4. **Code to adapt/reuse**: `code/U-SafeBench` for persona-conditioned evaluation and `code/AISafetyLab` for attack/eval orchestration.","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
